window.docContents[115].resolve({"/Type-______/____________/#example-inductive-types":{"contents":"A constructorless typeVacant 是一个空的归纳类型，相当于 Lean 的 Empty 类型：inductive Vacant : Type where\n空的归纳类型并不是没有用；它们可用于指示无法访问的代码。\n\nA constructorless propositionNo 是一个假 命题，等价于 Lean 的 False：inductive No : Prop where\n\n\nA unit typeSolo 相当于 Lean 的 Unit 类型：inductive Solo where\n  | solo\n这是归纳类型的示例，其中类型构造函数和构造函数的签名均被省略。\nLean 将 Solo 分配给 Type：#check Solo\nSolo : Type\n该构造函数被命名为 Solo.solo，因为构造函数名称是类型构造函数的命名空间。\n由于 Solo 不需要任何参数，因此为 Solo.solo 推断的签名为：#check Solo.solo\nSolo.solo : Solo\n\n\nA true propositionYes 等价于 Lean 的 True 命题：inductive Yes : Prop where\n  | intro\n与 One 不同，新的归纳类型Yes 被指定位于 Prop Universe 中。#check Yes\nYes : Prop\nYes.intro 推断的签名是：#check Yes.intro\nYes.intro : Yes\n\n\nA type with parameter and indexEvenOddList α b 是一个列表，其中 α 是列表中存储的数据类型，当条目数为偶数时，b 是 true：inductive EvenOddList (α : Type u) : Bool → Type u where\n  | nil : EvenOddList α true\n  | cons : α → EvenOddList α isEven → EvenOddList α (not isEven)\n此示例的类型正确，因为列表中有两个条目：example : EvenOddList String true :=\n  .cons \"a\" (.cons \"b\" .nil)\n此示例的类型不正确，因为列表中有三个条目：example : EvenOddList String true :=\n  .cons \"a\" (.cons \"b\" (.cons \"c\" .nil))\nType mismatch\n  EvenOddList.cons \"a\" (EvenOddList.cons \"b\" (EvenOddList.cons \"c\" EvenOddList.nil))\nhas type\n  EvenOddList String !!!true\nbut is expected to have type\n  EvenOddList String true\n在此声明中，α 是 参数，因为它在所有出现的 EvenOddList 中一致使用。\nb 是 索引，因为它在不同的情况下使用不同的 Bool 值。\n\nParameters before and after the colon在此示例中，两个参数均在 Either 签名中的冒号之前指定。inductive Either (α : Type u) (β : Type v) : Type (max u v) where\n  | left : α → Either α β\n  | right : β → Either α β\n在此版本中，有两种名为 α 的类型可能不相同：inductive Either' (α : Type u) (β : Type v) : Type (max u v) where\n  | left : {α : Type u} → {β : Type v} → α → Either' α β\n  | right : β → Either' α β\nMismatched inductive type parameter in\n  Either' α β\nThe provided argument\n  α\nis not definitionally equal to the expected parameter\n  α✝\n\nNote: The value of parameter `α✝` must be fixed throughout the inductive declaration. Consider making this parameter an index if it must vary.\n将参数放在冒号后面会产生可由构造函数实例化的参数：inductive Either'' : Type u → Type v → Type (max u v + 1) where\n  | left : {α : Type u} → {β : Type v} → α → Either'' α β\n  | right : β → Either'' α β\n此类型需要更大的 Universe，因为 构造函数参数必须位于比归纳类型的 Universe 小的 Universe 中。\nEither''.right 的类型参数是通过 Lean 的 自动隐式参数 的普通规则发现的。\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009Type System\u0009归纳类型\u0009归纳类型声明","header":"4.4.1.2. 示例归纳类型","id":"/Type-______/____________/#example-inductive-types"},"/Type-______/____________/#zh-classes-basicclasses-h007":{"contents":"A subsingleton is a type with at most one element. It is either empty or has a unique element.All propositions are subsingletons because of proof irrelevance: false propositions are empty, and\nall proofs of a true proposition are equal to one another. Some non-propositional types are also\nsubsingletons.Prove that α is a subsingleton by showing that any two elements are equal.Any two elements of a subsingleton are equal.\n\nIf a type is a subsingleton, then all of its elements are equal.\n\nIf two types are equal and one of them is a subsingleton, then all of their elements are\nheterogeneously equal.\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009Type 类别\u0009基础课程","header":"10.5.6. 子单例类型","id":"/Type-______/____________/#zh-classes-basicclasses-h007"},"/____________/____________/#by":{"contents":"\n\nTactic Proofs with by策略包含在使用 by 的术语中，后跟策略的序列，其中每个序列具有相同的缩进：或者，可以使用明确的大括号和分号：\n\n策略使用 by 术语调用。\n当精化器遇到 by 时，它会调用策略解释器来构造结果项。\n策略证明可以通过 by 嵌入到术语可能出现的任何上下文中。\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009策略样张","header":"14.1. 运行策略","id":"/____________/____________/#by"},"/mvcgen-______/_______________/#zh-vcgen-h004":{"contents":"有状态谓词通过entailment相关。\n有状态谓词的蕴含被定义为全称量化蕴涵：如果 P 和 Q 是状态 \\sigma 上的谓词，则当 ∀ s : \\sigma, P(s) → Q(s) 时，P 蕴含 Q（写作 P \\vdash_s Q）。\n\nEntailment in SPred.One predicate P entails another predicate Q if Q is true in every state in which P is true.\nUnlike implication (SPred.imp), entailment is not itself an SPred, but is instead an ordinary\nproposition.\n\nLogical equivalence of SPred.Logically equivalent predicates are equal. Use SPred.bientails.to_eq to convert bi-entailment to\nequality.\n\nNotation for SPredEntailment in SPred; sugar for SPred.entails.Tautology in SPred; sugar for SPred.entails ⌜True⌝.Bi-entailment in SPred; sugar for SPred.bientails.\n\n有状态谓词的逻辑包括蕴涵连接词。\n蕴涵和蕴涵之间的区别在于蕴涵是 Lean 逻辑中的语句，而蕴涵是状态逻辑的内部。\n给定状态 σ 的状态谓词 P 和 Q，P ⊢ₛ Q 是 Prop，而 spred(P → Q) 是 SPred σ。\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009mvcgen 策略\u0009谓词变压器\u0009状态谓词","header":"17.2.1.1. 蕴涵","id":"/mvcgen-______/_______________/#zh-vcgen-h004"},"/mvcgen-______/_______________/#zh-vcgen-h013":{"contents":"Hoare Triple 由前置条件、程序和后置条件组成。\n在前置条件为 true 的状态下运行程序会导致后置条件为 true 的状态。\n\nA Hoare triple for reasoning about monadic programs. A Hoare triple Triple x P Q is a\nspecification for x: if assertion P holds before x, then postcondition Q holds after\nrunning x.⦃P⦄ x ⦃Q⦄ is convenient syntax for Triple x P Q.\n\nHoare Triples⦃P⦄ x ⦃Q⦄ 是 Triple x P Q 的语法糖。\n\nConjunction for two Hoare triple specifications of a program x.\nThis theorem is useful for decomposing proofs, because unrelated facts about x can be proven\nseparately and then combined with this theorem.\n\nModus ponens for two Hoare triple specifications of a program x.\nThis theorem is useful for separating proofs. If h₁ : Triple x P₁ Q₁ proves a basic property about\nx and h₂ : Triple x P₂ (Q₁ →ₚ Q₂) is an advanced proof for Q₂ that builds on the basic proof\nfor Q₁, then mp x h₁ h₂ is a proof for Q₂ about x.\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009mvcgen 策略\u0009谓词变压器","header":"17.2.4. 霍尔三元组","id":"/mvcgen-______/_______________/#zh-vcgen-h013"}});